# Netlify redirects for KV Tree.
#
# PURPOSE: preserve SEO when the old www.kvtree.co.za site is replaced by this
# one. Every URL Google has indexed on the OLD site must 301-redirect to the
# best matching page here, or it becomes a 404 and that ranking is lost.
#
# HOW TO COMPLETE THIS FILE:
#   1. Inventory the old site's URLs (Google Search Console, its sitemap.xml,
#      or a Screaming Frog crawl) — see docs/website-transfer-guide.md.
#   2. Map each old path to the closest page on this site.
#   3. Add a line per URL below, using 301 (permanent). Remove the leading "# ".
#
# SYNTAX:  /old-path   /new-path   301
#
# EXAMPLES (commented out — replace with the real old URLs before launch):
# /index.html       /             301
# /services.html    /services     301
# /about-us         /about        301
# /about-us.html    /about        301
# /contact.php      /contact      301
# /gallery          /portfolio    301
# /tree-felling     /services     301
# /stump-removal    /services     301
#
# Note: www-vs-non-www canonicalisation is handled by Netlify's "primary
# domain" setting (set www.kvtree.co.za primary), not here.
#
# Leave no catch-all (/*) rule here — Next.js already serves a 404 for unknown
# paths, and a catch-all would mask URLs we still need to map.
